rounds.response:
With 9♥-8♠ the board is Q♦ T♦ 6♠ 9♦ Q♣ → I have two pair (Queens and Nines) with a Ten kicker (Q-Q-9-9-T).  
The only losing hand here is a better two-pair (T-9 would beat me by making Q-Q-T-9-9) or trips/trips diamond flush/full-house.

The villain just led for 30 on the river into a pot of 140. The bet is quite small (a little over 20 % pot), and the lone diamond comes on the turn so any made flush is pretty unlikely since they’d have had to defend flop out of position with exactly ♦J♦ or ♦K♦ and no pair, which is doubtful. Likewise a full house would probably have raised earlier.

Given the price (need to pay 30 to win 200) and that the villain could easily be bluffing missed back-door draws or value-betting a worse two-pair/ten-kicker, I have to call.

[Call]
